A shear stress $\sigma_{12}$ in the transverse plane gives a shear strain $\gamma_{12} =  rac{1}{G_{TT}} \sigma_{12}$, giving $S_{66} =  rac{1}{G_{TT}}$. For an isotropic plane, the shear modulus is related to the Young's modulus and Poisson's ratio by $G_{TT} =  rac{E_T}{2(1+
u_{TT})}$. This parameter is therefore not independent.

